Description.
Ocellar triangle brown, with ca. 2 or 3 setae above ocellar setae. Frons brownish yellow (
Fig. 5D
). Orb 
3
and Orb 
2
parallel (
Fig. 5D
). Pedicel brownish dark yellow; first flagellomere yellowish (
Fig. 5D
). Clypeus brownish yellow medially and brown laterally. Palpus yellow (
Fig. 5D
). Mesonotum mostly dark yellow (
Fig. 5E
). Postpronotal lobe brownish yellow (
Fig. 5F
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 12–14 irregular rows (
Fig. 5E
). Scutellum brownish yellow, brown to dark brown laterally, yellow at tip (
Fig. 5E
). Pleura, katepisternum, and mesopleuron mostly yellowish to yellow (
Fig. 5F
). Wing (
Fig. 2B
): with distinct patterns; costal vein between R 
2+3
and R 
4+5
distally with ca. 6 or 7 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
4+5
and M 
1
nearly parallel distally; halter yellow, usually with brownish to brown patches at stem and knob (
Fig. 5E
). Abdominal tergites dark brown, 2nd tergite yellowish medially and laterally, 3rd tergite nearly entirely yellowish except for sublateral region, setigerous laterally and on posterior margin, 5th tergite with a pair of yellow patches submedially in males (
Fig. 9B
); 2nd tergite yellow medially and laterally, 3rd to 6th tergites yellow submedially and laterally in females (
Fig. 9C
). Male terminalia: Epandrium pubescent, with ca. 14 setae near posterior and ventral margins per side (
Fig. 18A
). Cercus and surstylus pubescent (
Fig. 18A
). Paramere slender, narrow basally and apically (
Fig. 18C
).
